node.text:
I was craving something sweet for dessert so I whipped together this creamy Strawberry Tahini Smoothie Bowl #sponsoredbyninja. I topped it with berries, kiwi, hemp hearts and cacao nibs. This is something I wouldn’t mind having for breakfast when I’m in the mood for something sweet! I easily made it in my Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker.
.
This awesome device has a built-in tamper to blend and power through frozen and solid foods with less liquid for the thickest of smoothie bowls. 
.
The smartTORQUE™ is designed to power through heavy loads without stalling or the need to stir or shake. It makes the most thickest, and creamiest smoothies.
.
Strawberry Tahini Smoothie Bowl!
.
1 Frozen Banana 🍌.
1/2 cup Frozen Strawberries 🍓.
1 tablespoon honey 🍯 or maple syrup. 
1/2 cup oats.
1/4 cup tahini.
1/4 cup - 1/2 cup oat milk.
.
Add all ingredients to the @ninjakitchen Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker. Turn on and press the bowl button. Blend all ingredients well and turn the built-in tamper a few times to make sure it’s fully blended. Add to a bowl and top with all your favorite toppings. Find out more about the Ninja® Foodi®Smoothie Bowl Maker by clicking the link in my bio! #NinjaFoodiBlender

node.text:
#ad My family and I have been loving these @newmansown Cauliflower Crust Thin and Crispy Pizzas. My favorite is the Margherita, but also comes in a Cheese variety. It’s made with real cauliflower, real mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses, ripe tomatoes, and olive oil. I bake it in the oven, straight on the rack, for 12 minutes on 425 F and it comes out perfectly crispy every time! It’s also certified gluten-free.
.
Go visit @newmansown for the store locator to find out where to get your hands on some crispy crust cauliflower pizza goodness. #NewmansOwnPartner

node.title: Newman’s Own Cauliflower Crust Thin & Crispy Pizza

node.text: Keeping it simple with this fresh bowl of goodness for lunch today! Quinoa with baby kale tossed in fresh lemon juice, extra virgin olive oil, pecorino cheese and black pepper, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, kalamata olives and chopped Marcona almonds. It was a flavorful and nourishing bowl. Hope you’re having a great day!

node.text:
Slow Sunday’s call for Cinnamon Sweet Potato Waffles 🧇 with fresh berries 🍓🫐, crispy bacon 🥓, avocado 🥑 and a fried egg! 
.
These Cinnamon Sweet Potato Waffles 🧇 are soft and fluffy with just the right amount of sweetness and slight crispiness on the edges. Here’s how to make them:
.
Ingredients:
1 Large sweet potato.
1 cup of all purpose flour (sub gluten free)
1 tablespoon sweetener of choice.
1 teaspoon baking powder.
1 teaspoon cinnamon.
1 egg.
1 cup milk of choice.
1 tablespoon coconut oil.
1 teaspoon pure vanilla.
.
(1) Poke holes in the sweet potato (with peel left on) with a fork in 2-3 spots around the potato. Loosely wrap the sweet potato in a paper towel, place on a microwave safe plate and microwave on high for 4 1/2 minutes. Carefully slice the hot potato in half, let cool. 
(2) Heat your waffle iron to medium high heat. Use a spoon to scoop the cooked sweet potato out of the peel, add to a bowl and mash well. Add the flour, sweetener, baking powder and cinnamon and combine. 
(3) Add the remaining wet ingredients and mix well until it forms a batter like consistency. A few lumps in the batter is ok. (4) Pour ladle fulls of the batter into your waffle iron and cook each waffle 5-6 minutes depending on your waffle iron until the waffles are golden and fluffy. Makes 3-4 servings. Hope you’re having an amazing day!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Windermere, Florida. May be an image of food.

node.text: Veggie loaded brunches on the weekends are a must. A fried egg 🍳 with garlic butter mushrooms 🍄, steamed spinach 🍃, chili roasted chickpeas, baby  broccoli 🥦 and asparagus. The chickpeas, broccoli and asparagus were air roasted at the same time on the same pan on 400 F for 10 minutes. The recipe for the garlic butter mushrooms  can be found with link in bio. Hope you’re having a great weekend!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Winter Garden, Florida with @lovebeets.

node.text:
This Beet Panzanella salad 🥗 made with @lovebeets organic cooked beets is a wonderful way to enjoy the last few weeks of summer. Love Beets are on sale at Publix through 8/17 so now is a great opportunity to make this scrumptious salad. 
.
Those cherishing evenings eating outside with family and friends in the backyard around a fire pit with a cool breeze are the most funnest of times! This salad is fresh and cozy but most importantly it taste gooood!
.
To make the Summer Beet Panzanella Salad combine the following ingredients into a bowl. 
.
- 1/2 cup @lovebeets cut into 1 inch pieces. 
- 1 cup cherry tomatoes 🍅 sliced in half. 
- 1 cup English cucumber 🥒 cut into 1 inch pieces.
- 1/2 cup yellow bell pepper (or any color bell pepper) cut into 1 inch pieces. 
- 1/2 cup pitted kalamata olives or green castelventrano olives 🫒 . 
- 1/4 cup thin sliced red onion 🧅 .
- Feta cheese, goat cheese or fresh mozzarella balls your choice 🧀. 
- Loaf bread like a baguette 🥖, Italian or French bread cut into 1-2 inch cubes. 
- Extra virgin olive oil for drizzling.
- 1-2 tablespoons lemon 🍋 juice. 
- 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar. 
- Fresh basil 🌿 for garnish.
- salt and pepper.
. 
(1) Arrange bread cubes onto a sheet pan. Drizzle on olive oil, season with salt and pepper. Toss to combine and bake on 400 for 10 minutes until lightly toasty ….or toast in toaster oven for 4-5 minutes or until lightly golden. 
(2) In a large bowl combine @lovebeets organic cooked beets, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, red onion, bell pepper and kalamata olives. Drizzle in some olive oil, a few splashes of red wine vinegar and a few generous squeezes of fresh lemon juice. Toss together to combine. 
(3) Add the toasted bread to the bowl and lightly toss in the salad mixture to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Top with cheese and fresh basil. Serves 2-4.

node.text:
Good morning sunshine’s ☀️ A simple sweet and savory breakfast to start the day! 
.
Two scrambled eggs 🍳 and toasted English muffins topped with mashed avocado 🥑 and EBTB seasoning with strawberries 🍓, blueberries 🫐 and mandarin orange 🍊 segments. So darn good! Hope you have an amazing day 😊

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Windermere, Florida. May be an image of food.

node.text: A few good things for lunch today. Toasted sourdough with smashed avocado 🥑 and prosciutto, chili roasted chickpeas and arugula salad with banana peppers, cherry tomatoes 🍅, shredded Parmesan cheese 🧀, lemon juice 🍋 and extra virgin olive oil! Simple and yummy. The recipe for the chickpeas can be found with link in bio. I hope you’re having a great day!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Horizon West, Florida with @deepindiankitchen. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: My schedule has been crazy busy lately, and the preparation of my kids return to school this week made it even more crazy so preparing my own meals isn’t always an option. In this bowl I included @deepindiankitchen chickpea masala and spinach rice then added some more sautéed spinach 🍃, juicy ripe cherry tomatoes 🍅, avocado 🥑, red onion 🧅 and a fried egg 🍳 and it turned out to be a delicious and nourishing #meatlessmonday meal.  Hope the new week is off to a great start!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Windermere, Florida. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
Just because it’s the weekend doesn’t mean I still don’t enjoy a well balanced salad 🥗.
.
Mixed greens with, grape tomatoes 🍅, cucumber 🥒, chickpeas, avocado 🥑, banana pepper rings, kalamata olives, feta cheese, Italian dressing and tuna salad made with red onion, celery and mayo on top. It was a tasty and refreshing salad! Hope you’re having a great day.

node.text:
Enjoying this evening with a Mediterranean inspired mezze board and some good @robertmondavips wine, a perfect compliment to the Mediterranean flavors. #RMPSPartner 
.
Robert Mondavi Private Selection 100% Chardonnay is made only with Chardonnay grapes picked at the peak of ripeness from California vineyards for a pure and full expression of its classic varietals. It opens with aromas of citrus and toasty oak, followed by the pure expression of Chardonnay’s green apple, peach and citrus flavors. Aging on the lees in French and American oak naturally impart notes of vanilla and butter, and a rich, creamy mouthfeel.
.
Now is a great opportunity to try @robertmondavips wines and create your own paired board to enter the Battle of the Boards for a chance to win $25,000. Contest ends August 31, 2021. Robert Mondavi Private Selection Wines can be purchased at a store near you #For21 +

node.text: Toasting to the weekend with sourdough toast 🍞 topped with mashed avocado 🥑, juicy vine tomatoes 🍅, fresh cilantro 🌿, cracked black pepper and a sprinkle of sea salt. Probably one of my favorite combos ever. I hope you’re having a great day!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Windermere, Florida. May be an image of chow mein.

node.text: Colorful bowls 🌈 filled with all good things make me happy! I thought I would try something a little different today. Bibimbap with kimchi, carrot, snap peas, red bell pepper, spinach, fresh ginger and bean sprouts topped with a fried eggs, sesame seeds, a little tamari and and some gochujang. It was one delicious bowl. Happy Friday!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marlena Kur in Winter Garden, Florida. May be an image of food.

node.text:
This is a salad I often put on repeat because it’s well balanced, protein packed and super nourishing! Plus it’s super easy to throw together. 
.
Shredded rotisserie chicken with chickpeas, a hard boiled egg 🥚, tomatoes 🍅 and avocado 🥑 on a bed of romaine lettuce 🥬 with fresh parsley 🌿 lemon juice 🍋 and olive oil. As usual it really hit the spot. Hope you’re having a great day!
